  "notes": [
    "Nested-group replacement boundary workloads keep templates, captures, and haystacks intentionally tiny so the scorecard measures helper-call overhead for the newly supported bounded nested replacement-template slice rather than regex throughput.",
    "Measured rows cover the bounded `a((b))d` plus `\\\\1x` or `\\\\2x` and `a(?P<outer>(?P<inner>b))d` plus `\\\\g<outer>x` or `\\\\g<inner>x` `sub()`/`subn()` flows through module and compiled-`Pattern` entrypoints, while broader callable and quantified nested replacement shapes stay as explicit known-gap rows until the queued follow-ons land."
  ],
